1
00:00:14,948 --> 00:00:17,008
Mark? Mark?

2
00:00:17,084 --> 00:00:19,781
Mark, please ask your
father if he wants a burger.

3
00:00:19,853 --> 00:00:22,015
Mom. I know. You're
defending the free world.

4
00:00:22,089 --> 00:00:23,819
Please ask your Dad
if he wants a burger.

5
00:00:23,891 --> 00:00:25,325
Dad?

6
00:00:26,793 --> 00:00:31,197
Dad? Mom wants to
know if you want a burger.

7
00:00:34,635 --> 00:00:37,799
Mom, I don't know what
he wants. You ask him.

8
00:00:38,705 --> 00:00:40,298
Aunt Arlene!

9
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:45,372
Want a burger?

10
00:00:47,414 --> 00:00:48,507
Okay.

11
00:02:47,467 --> 00:02:50,096
The guy drove his wheelchair
into a pool. House would love that.

12
00:02:50,170 --> 00:02:53,732
He'll be bored. It's a great
visual, but it's diagnostically boring.

13
00:02:53,807 --> 00:02:56,606
What about
post-hair-transplant aphasia guy?

14
00:02:56,677 --> 00:02:59,557
Infection-throwing clots. House will
shoot it down and call you an idiot.

15
00:02:59,613 --> 00:03:01,104
Oh, well, we wouldn't want that.

16
00:03:01,181 --> 00:03:02,581
What about yoga girl?

17
00:03:02,649 --> 00:03:03,708
It has a good hook.

18
00:03:03,784 --> 00:03:05,184
Should we lead with it?

19
00:03:05,752 --> 00:03:09,484
His first day back, he might
want to flex his sarcasm muscle.

20
00:03:09,556 --> 00:03:12,492
Maybe we open with
one of the weaker pitches.

21
00:03:15,896 --> 00:03:17,524
You ran here?

22
00:03:18,565 --> 00:03:20,033
It's just eight miles.

23
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:21,261
Why did you...

24
00:03:21,334 --> 00:03:24,031
Why does a dog lick its
workplace-acceptable euphemism

25
00:03:24,104 --> 00:03:26,767
for testicles? Because he can.

26
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:27,950
What have you got for me, boss?

27
00:03:27,974 --> 00:03:30,534
I thought you said you
needed eight weeks of rehab.

28
00:03:30,610 --> 00:03:32,522
You should have been back
here... If I'd come back sooner,

29
00:03:32,546 --> 00:03:35,983
then I'd only be able to run six
miles. I never would have made it in.

30
00:03:36,049 --> 00:03:38,644
What have you got for me?
You're completely pain-free?

31
00:03:38,719 --> 00:03:40,278
The ketamine
treatment can wear off.

32
00:03:40,353 --> 00:03:42,151
It's been two months.
It's not wearing off.

33
00:03:42,222 --> 00:03:44,233
What have you got for me?
You can take as long as...

34
00:03:44,257 --> 00:03:47,318
Why are we having this discussion?
Want to hear me thank you again?

35
00:03:47,394 --> 00:03:49,693
Thank you, Doctor Cuddy,
not just for removing the bullet,

36
00:03:49,763 --> 00:03:51,808
but thank you for putting me
into a ketamine-induced coma

37
00:03:51,832 --> 00:03:54,358
and changing my
life. Happy? I am.

38
00:03:54,601 --> 00:03:57,332
Middle-aged man had hair
transplant about two months ago...

39
00:03:57,404 --> 00:04:00,203
Infection-throwing
clots. You're an idiot.

40
00:04:01,975 --> 00:04:04,069
Except you're not an idiot,

41
00:04:05,345 --> 00:04:08,372
and she is holding a file
for a 26-year-old female.

42
00:04:08,448 --> 00:04:10,576
What have you really got for me?

43
00:04:10,650 --> 00:04:13,916
Girl was doing an inverted
yoga pose, neck snapped,

44
00:04:13,987 --> 00:04:15,216
paralyzed from the neck down,

45
00:04:15,288 --> 00:04:18,918
except the x-rays show
no evidence of spinal injury.

46
00:04:19,926 --> 00:04:21,485
And she's cute.

47
00:04:21,561 --> 00:04:23,757
Oh, well played, sir.

48
00:04:28,101 --> 00:04:31,162
What about Stephen Hawking
trying to do the 500 butterfly?

49
00:04:31,238 --> 00:04:35,733
Forget it. Brain cancer, brain surgery.
There's nothing left to diagnose.

50
00:04:35,809 --> 00:04:37,539
I would take the other one.

51
00:04:37,611 --> 00:04:39,705
I'll take them both.

52
00:04:46,186 --> 00:04:47,950
You don't think he
had brain cancer?

53
00:04:48,021 --> 00:04:49,683
Of course he had brain cancer.

54
00:04:49,756 --> 00:04:52,055
Even oncologists don't
screw up for eight years.

55
00:04:52,125 --> 00:04:55,425
So if there's no diagnostic issue,
why are you taking the case?

56
00:04:55,495 --> 00:04:57,657
Treatment can be
interesting. Not to you.

57
00:04:57,731 --> 00:04:58,931
I've changed. No, you haven't.

58
00:04:58,999 --> 00:05:01,298
No, I haven't. So why
are you taking the case?

59
00:05:01,368 --> 00:05:02,666
The guy tried to kill himself.

60
00:05:02,736 --> 00:05:04,227
The guy had cancer. He's a lump.

61
00:05:04,304 --> 00:05:07,206
He hasn't been able to touch
his wife, speak to his kids.

62
00:05:07,274 --> 00:05:10,369
He's been in that chair for eight
years. His muscles have atrophied.

63
00:05:10,443 --> 00:05:12,207
Maybe I can help
him with the pain.

64
00:05:12,279 --> 00:05:13,823
Isn't that enough of a
reason to want to help?

65
00:05:13,847 --> 00:05:15,782
Not for you. I've changed.

66
00:05:15,849 --> 00:05:16,873
No, you haven't.

67
00:05:16,950 --> 00:05:19,419
Then why am I taking this case?

68
00:05:26,693 --> 00:05:29,458
Let's start with the cute
paraplegic. Welcome back.

69
00:05:29,529 --> 00:05:31,054
Hey. You look...

70
00:05:31,131 --> 00:05:32,360
Healthy.

71
00:05:37,671 --> 00:05:40,800
Quad with no broken
neck. Struck me as odd.

72
00:05:42,642 --> 00:05:45,635
You can take a whole two
minutes to ease into being back.

73
00:05:45,712 --> 00:05:47,647
I would've taken a whole
month to ease back,

74
00:05:47,714 --> 00:05:49,615
but eight weeks is the
maximum rehab time

75
00:05:49,683 --> 00:05:52,346
for a gunshot wound to the
stomach and neck, so go.

76
00:05:52,419 --> 00:05:54,820
We heard they never found
the guy. There's no new leads.

77
00:05:54,888 --> 00:05:56,968
What? You think he might
have shot this patient, too?

78
00:05:57,023 --> 00:05:59,219
It would explain her
symptoms. It could be MS.

79
00:05:59,292 --> 00:06:02,319
See? It's not so
difficult. It's not MS.

80
00:06:02,395 --> 00:06:05,126
She had no symptoms before
she climbed onto her head.

81
00:06:05,198 --> 00:06:08,293
Unless she's been upside-down
for the last 10 years, MS ain't it.

82
00:06:08,368 --> 00:06:11,347
Could be transverse myelitis, swelling
in the disks, choking off nerve function.

83
00:06:11,371 --> 00:06:13,465
MRI is negative for that.

84
00:06:17,978 --> 00:06:20,914
Your leg looks fine.
Totally pain-free?

85
00:06:21,147 --> 00:06:24,640
When did this turn into, "What did
you do over your summer vacation?"

86
00:06:24,718 --> 00:06:26,846
It's a little weird
to discuss the case

87
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:28,946
while you're staring at
your blood on the floor.

88
00:06:29,022 --> 00:06:31,582
I asked Cuddy to
replace the carpet.

89
00:06:33,293 --> 00:06:37,754
I like the carpet. What did
you do over the summer?

90
00:06:37,831 --> 00:06:39,026
Redo the tests.

91
00:06:39,099 --> 00:06:43,434
Let's see if the source of the problem
is in the limbs or the spine. Do an EMG.

92
00:06:44,704 --> 00:06:46,332
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

93
00:06:46,940 --> 00:06:51,275
We've got a whole other quad to cover.
This guy's still got fluid in his lungs.

94
00:06:51,344 --> 00:06:52,855
You don't think that's
from the pool he drank?

95
00:06:52,879 --> 00:06:55,940
Give him an O2 mask. His
leg muscles have atrophied.

96
00:06:56,016 --> 00:06:59,646
Tendons have shortened from
disuse, causing intense pain.

97
00:06:59,719 --> 00:07:02,746
Tendon surgery will make
him more comfortable.

98
00:07:03,123 --> 00:07:04,523
Comfortable?

99
00:07:06,693 --> 00:07:07,922
Scoot.

100
00:07:12,632 --> 00:07:14,498
Thanks for being here.

101
00:07:15,669 --> 00:07:17,160
Not a problem.

102
00:07:25,178 --> 00:07:26,703
My Dad wouldn't kill himself.

103
00:07:26,780 --> 00:07:28,806
You haven't spoken
to him in over six years.

104
00:07:28,882 --> 00:07:31,511
I know my dad. Mark,
the doctor's just trying to...

105
00:07:31,584 --> 00:07:34,679
- He wouldn't kill himself.
- Fine. I'm wrong.

106
00:07:35,522 --> 00:07:37,718
You obviously have a better
understanding of this man

107
00:07:37,791 --> 00:07:40,556
who drools in front of
your TV set 24 hours a day.

108
00:07:40,660 --> 00:07:42,185
Doctor House?

109
00:07:42,262 --> 00:07:45,460
Look, he must have been confused,
all right? It must have been an accident.

110
00:07:45,532 --> 00:07:47,967
I hope it was a suicide attempt.

111
00:07:48,034 --> 00:07:52,369
If he was trying to kill himself, then
he knows how miserable his life is.

112
00:07:52,439 --> 00:07:55,500
It means there's still
something there to kill.

113
00:07:56,209 --> 00:07:58,610
It means your dad's still there.

114
00:08:02,882 --> 00:08:04,441
Sorry. Need you.

115
00:08:04,517 --> 00:08:06,850
Thank you.

116
00:08:12,592 --> 00:08:16,256
We were doing the EMG, but we never got
past the insertion of the conduction pin.

117
00:08:16,329 --> 00:08:18,298
Did she just say, "Thank you"?

118
00:08:18,365 --> 00:08:20,698
I loaned her some
money. What went wrong?

119
00:08:20,767 --> 00:08:21,928
Nothing went wrong.

120
00:08:22,002 --> 00:08:23,937
If nothing went wrong,
then something went right.

121
00:08:24,004 --> 00:08:25,614
You're not gonna tell
me why she thanked you?

122
00:08:25,638 --> 00:08:27,834
You're not gonna tell
me what went right?

123
00:08:27,907 --> 00:08:32,811
You did something for which she
is grateful, and you're embarrassed?

124
00:08:32,879 --> 00:08:36,338
For you. She saw you coming up,
thought you were a 14 year-old boy.

125
00:08:36,416 --> 00:08:37,543
I set her straight.

126
00:08:37,617 --> 00:08:40,485
I am not telling you
what went wrong or right

127
00:08:40,553 --> 00:08:43,113
until you tell me why
she said, "Thank you."

128
00:08:43,189 --> 00:08:48,287
Oh, you got me. You know I
need to know. I am so gonna fold.

129
00:08:48,361 --> 00:08:51,991
Except you're forgetting
there's one thing I can do now.

130
00:08:55,001 --> 00:08:57,630
It's either that or
a reflex response.

131
00:08:58,271 --> 00:08:59,295
What happened?

132
00:08:59,372 --> 00:09:00,499
Okay.

133
00:09:00,573 --> 00:09:02,474
This is Doctor House.
House, this is Caren...

134
00:09:02,542 --> 00:09:04,067
Pleasure's all mine.
What happened?

135
00:09:04,144 --> 00:09:06,943
When we inserted the
conduction pin, she flinched.

136
00:09:07,013 --> 00:09:09,039
She flinched? Did you hear?

137
00:09:09,115 --> 00:09:10,326
Does that mean
I'm getting better?

138
00:09:10,350 --> 00:09:14,344
How big is a flinch? Bigger than
a twitch? Smaller than a spasm?

139
00:09:16,923 --> 00:09:18,983
Do you smoke?
Socially, not a lot.

140
00:09:19,059 --> 00:09:20,721
You do yoga, and you smoke?

141
00:09:20,794 --> 00:09:22,319
I know it's hypocritical, but...

142
00:09:22,395 --> 00:09:27,163
No, the world sees your legs.
No one's checking out your lungs.

143
00:09:27,233 --> 00:09:28,462
How would smoking cause...

144
00:09:28,535 --> 00:09:30,834
It wouldn't. I just
needed a lighter.

145
00:09:32,839 --> 00:09:34,671
House. Oh, my God!

146
00:09:36,943 --> 00:09:39,378
The case was looking so
promising. Hey, I'm not faking.

147
00:09:39,446 --> 00:09:42,177
You moved, therefore
you can move.

148
00:09:44,217 --> 00:09:47,381
Get this lunatic out of
here before she bores again.

149
00:09:47,454 --> 00:09:48,979
I'm not faking!

150
00:10:11,344 --> 00:10:15,782
I heard you were watching
surgery with a patient's family,

151
00:10:16,683 --> 00:10:19,482
talking to a patient's family.

152
00:10:21,254 --> 00:10:24,918
It's because of your hallucination,
isn't it? After you were shot.

153
00:10:24,991 --> 00:10:27,324
You chose life. You
decided you wanted meaning,

154
00:10:27,393 --> 00:10:32,354
so you took a case with no mystery,
something any doctor could do,

155
00:10:32,432 --> 00:10:36,460
a case with no upside
except the satisfaction

156
00:10:36,536 --> 00:10:38,767
of helping another human being.

157
00:10:40,206 --> 00:10:41,868
She thanked me.

158
00:10:41,941 --> 00:10:44,740
And you felt nothing.

159
00:10:46,379 --> 00:10:49,178
I wasn't sure what I
was supposed to feel.

160
00:10:50,817 --> 00:10:55,983
It's like your leg. It's atrophied.
Keep working it. The feeling will come.

161
00:10:56,055 --> 00:10:58,251
Sorry. Need you again.

162
00:10:58,324 --> 00:10:59,485
I told you to get rid of her.

163
00:10:59,559 --> 00:11:01,270
It's a good thing we didn't.
Tightness in her chest.

164
00:11:01,294 --> 00:11:03,172
She can't breathe. It
could be pleural effusion.

165
00:11:03,196 --> 00:11:07,156
Right. Either that or she's holding
her breath like a four-year-old.

166
00:11:17,977 --> 00:11:21,106
Relax. I'm not
gonna burn you again.

167
00:11:22,048 --> 00:11:24,142
I'm going to stab you!

168
00:11:30,890 --> 00:11:34,418
Look, either you're faking, or
you've got a pleural effusion.

169
00:11:34,494 --> 00:11:37,039
That's a buildup of fluid around
the lungs, which is very serious,

170
00:11:37,063 --> 00:11:39,542
and I would have no choice but to
stab you in the back with this needle

171
00:11:39,566 --> 00:11:42,195
and suck all of
the fluid out of you.

172
00:11:43,536 --> 00:11:46,096
So... CAMERON: We
should give her a local.

173
00:11:46,172 --> 00:11:49,199
That would defeat the
point of me being nasty.

174
00:11:49,842 --> 00:11:51,037
Ready?

175
00:11:59,919 --> 00:12:01,330
Down. She can't
breathe if she's down.

176
00:12:01,354 --> 00:12:02,447
Down. She can't...

177
00:12:02,522 --> 00:12:04,514
Down, down, down! Come on!

178
00:12:14,100 --> 00:12:15,625
That's not a pleural effusion.

179
00:12:15,702 --> 00:12:17,398
The problem's in her heart.

180
00:12:18,338 --> 00:12:20,136
Can't fake that.

181
00:12:31,884 --> 00:12:35,116
Had to relieve the pressure
three times in the last two hours,

182
00:12:35,188 --> 00:12:38,625
so either we figure out what's causing
blood to build up around her heart,

183
00:12:38,691 --> 00:12:40,903
or I follow her around with a
needle for the rest of her life.

184
00:12:40,927 --> 00:12:42,987
Echo was clean. No
structural abnormalities.

185
00:12:43,062 --> 00:12:45,224
It could be an
infectious process, TB.

186
00:12:45,298 --> 00:12:47,324
Or vasculitis would
also explain the effusion.

187
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:52,338
But not the paralysis. Let's
assume that she wasn't faking it.

188
00:12:52,405 --> 00:12:55,842
She moved, therefore she
could move. She wasn't paralyzed.

189
00:12:55,908 --> 00:12:58,844
Doesn't mean she was faking.
It could have been a delusion.

190
00:12:58,911 --> 00:13:00,436
Now, either she was faking

191
00:13:00,513 --> 00:13:02,482
and coincidentally got
a real cardiac problem

192
00:13:02,548 --> 00:13:05,074
at the exact same
time, or it's a delusion,

193
00:13:05,151 --> 00:13:08,280
and the fake paralysis is a
real neurological symptom.

194
00:13:08,354 --> 00:13:10,380
Are you thinking vascular
tumor on her spine?

195
00:13:10,456 --> 00:13:11,549
Her platelets are normal.

196
00:13:11,624 --> 00:13:13,684
And she's been scanned
up and down. It's all clean.

197
00:13:13,760 --> 00:13:15,854
So open her up and find it.

198
00:13:16,596 --> 00:13:18,707
So what do you want us
to do? Just start at her neck

199
00:13:18,731 --> 00:13:21,792
and just keep on cutting down her
spine until we stumble on something?

200
00:13:21,868 --> 00:13:23,496
That should work.

201
00:13:30,576 --> 00:13:33,011
His heart rate's a little
high. Should I be worried?

202
00:13:33,079 --> 00:13:36,140
Probably just means he's still
in discomfort from the surgery.

203
00:13:36,215 --> 00:13:38,650
I'm gonna up his
morphine a little.

204
00:13:38,718 --> 00:13:40,744
You've been so nice to us.

205
00:13:40,820 --> 00:13:42,379
It's the job.

206
00:13:42,455 --> 00:13:46,290
No, I mean, all the other doctors, all
they did was obsess on the cancer,

207
00:13:46,359 --> 00:13:50,455
the treatment, the
damage, just trying to fix him.

208
00:13:51,230 --> 00:13:55,497
You're the first doctor that's ever
given a damn about the quality of his life.

209
00:13:58,438 --> 00:14:02,239
His heart rate's come down.
The morphine worked. I was right.

210
00:14:07,213 --> 00:14:10,809
What a touching moment.
That's why we become doctors,

211
00:14:10,883 --> 00:14:13,512
for these rare moments
when our hearts are warmed...

212
00:14:13,586 --> 00:14:15,817
Would you like to get a drink?

213
00:14:16,189 --> 00:14:18,658
Are you serious, or are you
just trying to change the subject?

214
00:14:18,725 --> 00:14:20,557
No, I'm serious.

215
00:14:20,626 --> 00:14:26,088
I drink. You drink. We could do it
at the same time, the same table.

216
00:14:27,233 --> 00:14:29,668
If you eat, we
could do that, too.

217
00:14:31,738 --> 00:14:34,799
I mean, if the answer's
no, that's cool, but...

218
00:14:37,477 --> 00:14:42,916
No, it's just you're just coming off of
surgery, and you're not yourself yet,

219
00:14:42,982 --> 00:14:46,714
and I work for you, and
even though last year's...

220
00:14:47,954 --> 00:14:51,049
You're smiling. I'm saying
no, and you're smiling.

221
00:14:51,124 --> 00:14:54,891
Well, don't take it personally.
It's just 'cause you're full of crap.

222
00:14:54,961 --> 00:14:59,126
You have no interest in going out with
me. Maybe you did, when I couldn't walk,

223
00:14:59,198 --> 00:15:02,657
when I was a sick puppy that
you could nurture back to health.

224
00:15:02,735 --> 00:15:05,637
Now that I'm healthy,
there's nothing in it for you.

225
00:15:06,806 --> 00:15:09,037
You are not healthy.

226
00:15:11,444 --> 00:15:13,345
Cuddy wants to see you.

227
00:15:21,421 --> 00:15:23,413
You've been back
at work 24 hours,

228
00:15:23,489 --> 00:15:26,926
and you're already playing
hide-and-seek in a woman's spine.

229
00:15:26,993 --> 00:15:28,086
Who won the pool?

230
00:15:28,161 --> 00:15:29,595
There's no tumor.

231
00:15:29,662 --> 00:15:31,494
Her platelets are
normal. The scans didn't...

232
00:15:31,564 --> 00:15:36,059
What's the worst that can happen?
Might paralyze her. She won't even notice.

233
00:15:36,135 --> 00:15:38,866
Her lawyers might. You're
not doing the surgery.

234
00:15:38,938 --> 00:15:40,804
And lower the morphine
on your other patient.

235
00:15:40,873 --> 00:15:43,934
Fine, I'll lower it if you
let me do the surgery.

236
00:15:44,010 --> 00:15:46,707
What? You want to trade?

237
00:15:47,346 --> 00:15:51,113
